00:56:28.960 --> 00:56:33.030 align:middle line:90%
So due to translation symmetry--

00:56:33.030 --> 00:56:37.250 align:middle line:84%
so we expect energy
momentum conservation.

00:56:37.250 --> 00:56:50.090 align:middle line:90%


00:56:50.090 --> 00:56:52.340 align:middle line:84%
OK, so yeah, so
this, if you write it

00:56:52.340 --> 00:56:57.570 align:middle line:84%
in terms of the
component rotation,

00:56:57.570 --> 00:57:02.690 align:middle line:84%
so this is delta beta
alpha plus i T beta alpha.

00:57:02.690 --> 00:57:05.630 align:middle line:84%
OK, and i just
purely convention.

00:57:05.630 --> 00:57:07.820 align:middle line:84%
i is purely convention,
just for convenience.

00:57:07.820 --> 00:57:12.930 align:middle line:90%


00:57:12.930 --> 00:57:14.970 align:middle line:84%
So due to the momentum
conservation--

00:57:14.970 --> 00:57:17.830 align:middle line:90%


00:57:17.830 --> 00:57:20.530 align:middle line:84%
so this corresponding
to the interaction part.

00:57:20.530 --> 00:57:23.310 align:middle line:84%
So in this part, we expect
alpha not equal to beta

00:57:23.310 --> 00:57:26.230 align:middle line:90%
because you have interactions.

00:57:26.230 --> 00:57:28.270 align:middle line:84%
But the total momentum
must be conserved.

00:57:28.270 --> 00:57:33.550 align:middle line:84%
So the sum of here must
be the sum of here.

00:57:33.550 --> 00:57:37.320 align:middle line:84%
Just the total momentum
must be conserved.

00:57:37.320 --> 00:57:41.720 align:middle line:84%
So that means this scene
must contain a delta function

00:57:41.720 --> 00:57:43.670 align:middle line:84%
between the total
initial momentum

00:57:43.670 --> 00:57:46.970 align:middle line:90%
and the total final momentum.

00:57:46.970 --> 00:57:50.345 align:middle line:84%
And so we can just
convenient to extract--

00:57:50.345 --> 00:57:53.047 align:middle line:90%


00:57:53.047 --> 00:57:54.380 align:middle line:90%
to separate that delta function.

00:57:54.380 --> 00:58:08.460 align:middle line:84%
OK, so convenient to write
i T beta alpha equal to i,

00:58:08.460 --> 00:58:10.340 align:middle line:84%
you separate out
this delta function.

00:58:10.340 --> 00:58:13.640 align:middle line:84%
Because we know the delta
function must be there,

00:58:13.640 --> 00:58:15.500 align:middle line:90%
so p alpha minus p beta.

00:58:15.500 --> 00:58:18.950 align:middle line:84%
So p alpha and p beta
means total momentum

00:58:18.950 --> 00:58:20.060 align:middle line:90%
for alpha and the beta.

00:58:20.060 --> 00:58:23.630 align:middle line:90%
And then, you have M alpha beta.

00:58:23.630 --> 00:58:25.310 align:middle line:90%
So this is the nontrivial part.

00:58:25.310 --> 00:58:26.850 align:middle line:90%
So this part is trivial.

00:58:26.850 --> 00:58:28.700 align:middle line:90%
You expect from kinematics.

00:58:28.700 --> 00:58:30.770 align:middle line:84%
And so this M alpha
beta is called

00:58:30.770 --> 00:58:32.720 align:middle line:90%
